                        <li><strong>Unicellular</strong> — made of a single cell (e.g., <em>Amoeba</em>, <em>Chlamydomonas</em>, <em>Paramecium</em>, bacteria).</li>
                        <li><strong>Multicellular</strong> — made of many cells (e.g., fungi, plants, animals).</li>
