                    <h2>2.3.3 Lysosomes — The "Suicide Bags"</h2>
                    <p><strong>Lysosomes</strong> are single-membrane sacs filled with powerful digestive (hydrolytic) enzymes, made by the RER.</p>
                    <p><strong>Functions:</strong> Waste disposal, digest worn-out organelles, attack pathogens.</p>
                    <p>Called <strong>"Suicide Bags"</strong> because if a cell is badly damaged, lysosomes can burst and digest the entire cell from inside (<strong>autolysis</strong>).</p>
