                    <h3>🧬 Meiosis — Reproduction</h3>
                    <p>1 cell divides <strong>twice</strong> to make <strong>4 non-identical gamete cells</strong> (sperm/egg) with <strong>half</strong> the original chromosome number.</p>
                    <div class="analogy-box">
                        <strong>🃏 Card Deck Shuffling</strong>
                        <p>Meiosis is like splitting a deck of 52 cards into 4 smaller, shuffled hands — each hand gets half the original number and a unique mix.</p>
